article.headline: St. Peter's three-game winning streak ends
article.linkText: DePaul spanks St. Peter's behind Smith's 32 pts.
article.story:
JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) -- Khara Smith scored a season-high 32 points and added 13 rebounds and five blocked shots as DePaul (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today, No. 19 AP) beat St. Peter's 86-61 on Tuesday night.

Allie Quigley finished had season highs of 24 points and eight assists and was 5-of-9 from 3-point range for DePaul (8-2). Khalisha Harris had 18 points and nine rebounds for St. Peter's (4-4).

DePaul held the lead for most of the game, but St. Peter's stayed close until midway through the second half, when the Blue Demons went on a 25-2 run. Quigley had nine points during the outburst, while Smith added eight.

Jannie Dant finished with 10 points and 10 assists for DePaul.

Tiffany Jones added 14 points and Kristen Hood 11 for St. Peter's, which had won its last three games.
